    • damageCalc

      int damageCalc(Skill attack, Pokemon enemy) throws IllegalStateException, IllegalArgumentException
      Method damageCalc() calculates and returns an integer value for the damage that this Pokemon would inflict on an enemy Pokemon using a given attack. Damage considers the user attack, enemy defense, and type matching between the attack Skill and the enemy Pokemon
      Parameters:
      attack - Skill: attack to use against the enemy Pokemon
      enemy - Pokemon: Pokemon getting attacked by this Pokemon
      Returns:
      Int: damage value this Pokemon inflicts to enemy Pokemon with the attack Skill
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - when the input attack Skill is not in this.skills list
      IllegalArgumentException - when this or enemy Pokemon have status Status.FAINTED

    • statChange

      ArrayList<String> statChange(double attackChange, double defenseChange, double speedChange) throws IllegalStateException
      Method statChange() applies stat changes to this Pokemon's currentStats. Attack, defense, and speed stats may be affected.
      Parameters:
      attackChange - double: percent change to this Pokemon's attack stat
      defenseChange - double: percent change to this Pokemon's defense stat
      speedChange - double: percent change to this Pokemon's speed stat
      Returns:
      ArrayList: list of String values that represent the stat changes that happened when running statChange()
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - when this Pokemon is not Battling

    • attack

      ArrayList<String> attack(Skill attack, Pokemon enemy) throws IllegalArgumentException, IllegalStateException
      Method attack() uses an attack Skill to inflict damage and apply stat buffs / debuffs to this and the enemy Pokemon
      Parameters:
      attack - Skill: attack Skill this Pokemon uses to attack
      enemy - Pokemon: enemy Pokemon struck by the attack Skill
      Returns:
      ArrayList: list of strings representing the actions that occur as a result of the attack. Potential items include: attack used, enemy pokemon has fainted, the user has been buffed / debuffed, or the enemy has been buffed / debuffed
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - when this or the enemy Pokemon are not Battling
      IllegalArgumentException - when the input attack Skill is not in this.skills list

    • takeDamage

      ArrayList<String> takeDamage(int damage) throws IllegalArgumentException, IllegalStateException
      Method takeDamage() applies damage to this Pokemon. If the currentHealth of this Pokemon goes down to 0, then the Pokemon's status changes to fainted
      Parameters:
      damage - Int: amount of damage to do to this Pokemon
      Returns:
      ArrayList: list of Strings that represent actions that have occurred
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - when damage value is negative
      IllegalStateException - when the Pokemon is not actively battling
